CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 30, 1946, pg. 26, reads: "Favorites - Favored to cop honors in Section I of the American Amateur Basketball League are the smooth working lads of the Centre Avenue 'Y' Big Five.  This year's team has been strengthened by the acquisition of three former college stars.  Shown, left to right, standing are Robinson (manager); Childs, Stevenson, Dowdy, Redmond, Lewis, Taylor (coach).  Seated: Ellis, Butler, W. Ford, A. Ford and Austin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Centre Avenue YMCA basketball team, seated from left: Ellis, Butler, W. Ford, A. Ford, Austin; standing: manager Robinson, Childs, Stevenson, Dowdy, Redmond, Lewis, and coach Bennie Taylor
